The AWS_Trusted_Advisor_for_Splunk app allows you to pull in your AWS Trusted Advisor data into Splunk.

### Version Support: ###
- Splunk 7.0, 7.1


### Setup: ###
1. Once the app is installed, go to the app manager screen, find the AWS_Trusted_Advisor_for_Splunk app and click 'Set Up'
2. On the setup screen fill in your AWS 'Access Key', 'Secret Key', and 'Region'. All fields are required.
3. The IAM user associated with your AWS connection must have access to 'AWS Support' [https://aws.amazon.com/premiumsupport/]
in AWS in order to pull in the Trusted Advisor data.
4. You may force run the input by restarting Splunk. Once restart has completed, you should see data by searching
sourcetype="trusted_advisor"


### How it works: ###
- The scripted input runs at 12:30am nightly to pull in your AWS Trusted Advisor information.
    Note: AWS Trusted Advisor sends out a weekly report, so you most likely won't be receiving data more frequently than
    every 7 days.
- The data goes into a sourcetype called 'trusted_advisor'.
- A saved search called 'Trusted Advisor Checks Lookup Populator' populates a lookup called 'trusted_advisor_checks.csv'.
This lookup can be used to enrich the 'trusted_advisor' Sourcetype, which only provides the Check's ID by default


### Knowledge Objects: ###
#Saved Searches: #
- Trusted Advisor Checks Lookup Populator: Scheduled to run the 1st of every month. Is meant to populate Trusted Advisor Checks
information into 'trusted_advisor_checks.csv'. This lookup will run automatically for the first time once you have provided
your AWS credentials in the setup page.

# Dashboard: #
- Trusted Advisor dashboard provides a high level overview of all your Trusted Advisor checks. You can drill-down into
the Overview panel to view specific Resource information.

# Lookups #
- trusted_advisor_checks.csv - pulls in Check information using the | getchecks custom command. See below for more info.
- ta_categories.csv - maps underscored category names with 'clean' category names. For use on the 'Trusted Advisor' dashboard.


### Custom Commands ###
- The `| getchecks` command is a generating command that pulls in Trusted Advisor Checks information.
- The following information is pulled about a specific check:
            'id': 'string',
            'name': 'string',
            'description': 'string',
            'category': 'string',
            'metadata': [
                'string',
            ]
- This custom command is used in the 'Trusted Advisor Checks Lookup Populator' described above.


### Example Searches:
`sourcetype=trusted_advisor | lookup trusted_advisor_checks.csv`


### Debugging Issues: ###
- If the app encounters any errors when attempting to authenticate with AWS they will show up in the Messages dropdown.
- Dashboard is still empty after configuring the app:
    - Make sure that the AWS credentials you provided are valid and that your credentials have access to pull data
    from AWS' Premium Support. This would be configured through AWS' IAM settings.
    - Check the 'Messages' dropdown in the top black bar in Splunk to see if any error messages were thrown.
    - Check the 'trusted_advisor_checks.csv' lookup to see if it contains any data. If not:
        - Try populating the lookup manually by running `| getchecks | outputlookup trusted_advisor_checks.csv`
        - If that fails, then your credentials are most likely incorrect or do not have access to AWS Premium Support.


### Release Notes: ###
